{"metadata":{"title":"Discover and curate Swift Packages using Collections","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC21","role":"sampleCode"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true}]},{"text":"Related Sessions","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Related-Sessions"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10192-Whats-new-in-Swift","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-408-Adopting-Swift-Packages-in-Xcode","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-410-Creating-Swift-Packages"],"type":"links","style":"list"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10197-Discover-and-curate-Swift-Packages-using-Collections"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10197-discover-and-curate-swift-packages-using-collections"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21"]]},"kind":"article","sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Whether you’re curating packages for your team, for education purposes, or to share with other developers, Swift Package Collections can help you discover, explore and import new packages into your project. Discover improvements in the Swift Package workflow using Collections, and learn how you can curate, create, sign, and share your own Swift Package Collections."}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2021\/10197","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (14 min)"}},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","title":"WWDC Notes","images":[{"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","type":"icon"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","title":"Learn More…","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"WWDC21-Icon.png":{"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC21-Icon.png","type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-408-Adopting-Swift-Packages-in-Xcode":{"role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"Swift packages are a great way to organize and share code, and are now supported while building apps for all Apple platforms in Xcode 11. Find out how to use community-developed packages in your project, how Swift packages are structured, and how package versioning and dependencies work.","type":"text"}],"title":"Adopting Swift Packages in Xcode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-408-adopting-swift-packages-in-xcode","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-408-Adopting-Swift-Packages-in-Xcode","kind":"article"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21","title":"WWDC21","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC21-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identi